### 3C тАФ Login Attempt Tracking & Account Lockout

#### [NEW] [login_attempts table / model]

```python
class LoginAttempt(db.Model):
    __tablename__ = 'login_attempts'
    id = db.Column(db.Integer, primary_key=True)
    identifier = db.Column(db.String(200), nullable=False)  # email/username tried
    ip_address = db.Column(db.String(50))
    success = db.Column(db.Boolean, default=False)
    attempted_at = db.Column(db.DateTime, default=lambda: datetime.now(timezone.utc))
```

#### [MODIFY] [auth_controller.py](file:///c:/Users/pc/Documents/Github/server/app/controllers/auth_controller.py)

- Log every login attempt (success/fail) to `login_attempts` table
- Before authenticating, check failed attempts in the last `lockoutDurationMinutes` тАФ if count тЙе `maxLoginAttempts`, return `429 Too Many Attempts`
- Show failed attempt count in the Security tab UI

### 3D тАФ Additional Security Features (Suggested)

These are **additional features** to consider for the Security tab:

| Feature | Description | Effort |
|---------|-------------|--------|
| **Password Expiry** | Force password change after N days (configurable, 0 = disabled) | Medium |
| **IP Allowlist** | Restrict admin access to specific IP addresses/ranges | Medium |
| **Force Logout All** | Button to blacklist all active tokens for the org (emergency) | Small |
| **Active Sessions** | Show list of active admin sessions (token JTI, IP, last activity) | Medium |
| **Login History** | Display recent login attempts (success/fail) with IP and timestamp | Small |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Recommendation**: For this implementation round, I suggest implementing **3A (2FA)**, **3B (Session Timeout)**, **3C (Login Attempts)**, **Force Logout All**, and **Login History**. Password Expiry and IP Allowlist can be deferred to a future update.

